    "In addition to providing basic support, chatbots can boost engagement with mental health interventions [37] [38] [39] [40] [41] and pairing a message with an engagement opportunity (e.g., to complete a mindfulness activity) leads to more goal-oriented behaviors [42].",
    "Early tests of genAI-based, mental health chatbots have led to mixed results; although many effective deliver evidence-based interventions and offer empathetic support, they can also get confused and offer nonsense responses [35, [43] [44] [45].",
    "There are also examples of genAI tools providing responses that are not evidence-based and may be harmful [46] [47] [48] [49].",
    "Suicide is among the most sensitive mental health topics.",
    "Anonymous phone and text lines provide crucial support to people who are thinking of ending their lives."
